definition: Slovakia/Slovak/abbr. for 斯洛伐克[Si1 luo4 fa2 ke4]

sentences.english: Hello, I've a person-to-person call from London for Mr. Stanley.
sentences.chinese: 喂，我有一個倫敦打給斯坦利先生的叫人電話。

sentences.english: it's more of like the investment banks, you know, the Morgan Stanley, and the Goldman Sachs.
sentences.chinese: 更可能想到投資銀行，如摩根斯坦利，還有高盛。

sentences.english: But Vancouver has never won the Stanley Cup.
sentences.chinese: 但是溫哥華從來沒有贏得斯坦利杯。

sentences.english: I love the history of the Stanley Cup.
sentences.chinese: 我愛的斯坦利杯的歷史。

sentences.english: Morgan Stanley (IIF) has issued a report recommending to buy shares of Spreadtrum Communications Inc (NASDAQ: SPRD).
sentences.chinese: 摩根斯坦利最近發表的一份報告中推薦買入展訊通訊。
這是斯坦利費什的觀點。

sentences.english: Rescorla taught Morgan Stanley employees to save themselves.
sentences.chinese: Rescorla教會摩根斯坦利的員工拯救自己。

sentences.english: Hello, I have a person-to-person call from London for Mr. Stanley.
sentences.chinese: 喂，我有一個從倫敦打給斯坦利先生的叫人電話。

sentences.english: Morgan Stanley dropped HBGary as a security contractor.
sentences.chinese: 摩根斯坦利不再聘用HBGary作爲安全承包商。

sentences.english: The bidding process will be managed by Morgan Stanley.
sentences.chinese: 該競價過程將由摩根斯坦利公司管理。

sentences.english: Like the Hall itself, the Stanley Cup has changed over the years.
sentences.chinese: 霍爾本身一樣，斯坦利杯多年來已經改變。
斯坦利覺得這麼做很愚蠢，但還是感到些許寬慰。
